Global Warming Poses Threat to Public Health.
NEW YORK July 8 (Xinhua) United Nations health and environmental agencies warn that global warming due to air pollution The warning is given in a report due to be issued today when international negotiations on global warming resume in Geneva.
Scientists have become more and more concerned about the possible health consequences of global warming.
They believe that the earth climate will change rapidly in the coming century as pollution in the atmosphere traps solar radiation the so called greenhouse effect.
